data.description: Welcome to the gorgeous Historic 1929 E. Q. Benbow house!  The spacious handsomely detailed 1-1/2 story brick bungalow sits just a couple of minutes from downtown Mount Airy and all the wonderful activities, shops and restaurants it offers!  The large attached front porch, with wide gabled entry bay extends across the main elevation to the north to encompass a Porte Cochere.  Heavy battered brick piers support the porch.  Both the porch gable and an offset gabled dormer feature rough stucco and applied wooden trim imitative of half-timbering and are lighted by Palladian windows.  The main entrance is composed of leaded glass sidelights and a multi-paned door.  The lot has a beautiful level and fenced back yard and is flanked by a 2 car brick garage.  Inside the home features 4 bedrooms (with possibilities for a 5th), living and sitting rooms, dining room, laundry room and an immaculate kitchen! Has been successfully used as a VRBO on a limited basis. This home is an absolute MUST SEE.
